main event: Military aircrews operating over the Pacific Ocean observed several unidentified flying objects on both visual and radar.
interesting points: The objects appeared as bright lights or luminous bodies moving at high speed and exhibiting erratic movement.
Radar contact and visual observation corroborated that the objects were real, solid bodies moving at high speed and altitude.
This was one of several similar reports of unusual aerial phenomena observed by military aircrews in the Pacific during this period.
No photographs were available, but the report concluded that several unidentified objects were observed both visually and on radar.
The objects were tracked on radar and appeared solid and real, not anomalous propagation.
sighted object: several bright lights or luminous bodies
